{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What is happening here?{\r}

108
00:11:31,238 --> 00:11:33,323
一个杂种和他的娼妓母亲
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}A bastard and a whore mother{\r}

109
00:11:42,082 --> 00:11:43,375
住手！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Stop!{\r}

110
00:11:43,542 --> 00:11:44,918
退下！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Fall back!{\r}

111
00:11:46,086 --> 00:11:47,671
退下！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Fall back!{\r}

112
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,218
- 放下剑　- 我不放
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Put the sword down! - I will not!{\r}

113
00:11:52,426 --> 00:11:55,389
- 杀了他　- 再动他就死
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Kill him! - Try and he dies first!{\r}

114
00:11:56,764 --> 00:11:58,141
你在做什么，兄弟？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What is it that you want, brother?{\r}

115
00:11:58,766 --> 00:12:01,519
看起来我的同类要明天上午才能走
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}It seems as though my kind travel in the morning.{\r}

116
00:12:02,562 --> 00:12:04,230
但我也想他们得到应有的保护
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I want them to have a proper escort.{\r}

117
00:12:08,526 --> 00:12:11,446
再动一下，我就把刀插到你头上
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Move again, and I will bury this in your skull!{\r}

118
00:12:12,781 --> 00:12:13,865
你叫什么名字？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What's your name?{\r}

119
00:12:14,366 --> 00:12:15,409
忒修斯
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Theseus.{\r}

120
00:12:15,617 --> 00:12:18,161
我们没时间在这应付内乱，忒修斯，放开他
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Now is not the time for violence Theseus. Let him go.{\r}

121
00:12:19,413 --> 00:12:21,832
除非你承诺会保护我们所有人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Only if I have your word the rest of the village will be protected.{\r}

122
00:12:22,541 --> 00:12:23,792
我向你保证
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You have my word.{\r}

123
00:12:24,001 --> 00:12:26,170
我会留下几个明天能保护你们的人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I will leave capable men for the caravan tomorrow.{\r}

124
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:32,343
- 杀了这叛徒　- 你他妈的还想怎样！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Kill this traitor! - I will not have a spectacle!{\r}

125
00:12:33,970 --> 00:12:35,763
把他给我绑了，别在这里碍老子的眼！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Restrain him! Get him outta my sight!{\r}

126
00:12:37,765 --> 00:12:39,183
把他带走
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Take him away.{\r}

127
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:46,483
留着你的体力，忒修斯，还需要你对付赫拉克里恩大军呢
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Save your blood lust for Heraklion veins, Theseus.{\r}

128
00:12:47,275 --> 00:12:49,319
加入我们军团吧，看你有两下子，哪学的？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Join our ranks.You have been trained well.{\r}

129
00:12:51,530 --> 00:12:53,615
我有一个好老师
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I had a good teacher.{\r}

130
00:12:53,907 --> 00:12:57,077
你来当我的左右手，我们一起对付亥伯龙军团
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I could use a man of your skill at my side to defeat Hyperion's legions.{\r}

131
00:12:57,411 --> 00:12:58,745
我为什么要帮你？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Why would I serve you?{\r}

132
00:12:59,663 --> 00:13:01,373
你们这么瞧不起我们
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You would have so easily abandoned us...{\r}

133
00:13:02,458 --> 00:13:04,335
妈，我们走
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Let's go, Mother.{\r}

134
00:13:09,882 --> 00:13:13,552
雷山德，你不再是我军团成员
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Lysander, you are no longer part of this army.{\r}

135
00:13:16,514 --> 00:13:19,308
一会把你的武器盾牌都给我上缴了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Relinquish your shield and your spear{\r}

136
00:13:20,518 --> 00:13:22,478
待在这儿明天和他们一起走
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}and remain here to travel with the peasants tomorrow.{\r}

137
00:13:22,687 --> 00:13:24,481
- 你都看见了…　- 就这样
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- But you saw him... - It is done.{\r}

138
00:13:31,488 --> 00:13:32,989
回头见
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}See you later.{\r}

139
00:13:36,618 --> 00:13:37,869
你的行李呢，前辈？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Where are your things, old man?{\r}

140
00:13:37,869 --> 00:13:41,030
你准备好撤退没有？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Are you not prepared for the march?{\r}

141
00:13:41,999 --> 00:13:45,210
战争是给你们肌肉男和野心家的游戏
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Such odysses were meant for the young people and expectant.{\r}

142
00:13:46,003 --> 00:13:49,089
不适合像我这样的老人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Not for a worn out old goat like me.{\r}

143
00:13:49,381 --> 00:13:51,092
请你再考虑清楚
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Please reconsider.{\r}

144
00:13:51,342 --> 00:13:53,177
留在这里等于自杀
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You know staying here is suicide.{\r}

145
00:13:54,011 --> 00:13:57,932
如果赫拉克里恩人来了，兴许我还能死的爽快点
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}If the Heraklians show up at least I'll be spared a slow death.{\r}

146
00:13:58,808 --> 00:14:02,270
至少我知道，他们下手可不会犹豫不决的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}From what I understand, indecision is not their style{\r}

147
00:14:04,481 --> 00:14:06,399
你真疯狂！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You are mad.{\r}

148
00:14:08,568 --> 00:14:10,820
只是太累了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Just tired.{\r}

149
00:14:12,531 --> 00:14:16,994
活着并不是最重要的事情，忒修斯
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}It's not living as such that's important Theseus.{\r}

150
00:14:17,786 --> 00:14:20,330
而是活的有尊严
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}It's living rightly.{\r}

151
00:14:26,921 --> 00:14:29,854
我从没见过像打仗那样勇猛凶残的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}They fight with a ferocity unlike anything I've seen.{\r}

152
00:14:31,175 --> 00:14:34,132
他们眼睛都能看透黑夜似的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Almost as if they could see in the darkness.{\r}

153
00:14:35,418 --> 00:14:37,007
要多彪悍有多彪悍
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}It's always suited them.{\r}

154
00:14:37,723 --> 00:14:39,350
说的他们跟神一样
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You speak as if they are not human.{\r}

155
00:14:40,018 --> 00:14:41,686
他们是人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}There are human.{\r}

156
00:14:41,894 --> 00:14:44,606
他们也是赫拉克里恩人，和我们一样
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}They're Heraklians, they bleed just as we do.{\r}

157
00:14:45,106 --> 00:14:48,401
唯一的区别是他们为信仰而战
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}The only difference is they fight for a belief{\r}

158
00:14:48,610 --> 00:14:51,446
因此他们下手异常凶狠
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}which allows them to kill without restraint.{\r}

159
00:14:51,863 --> 00:14:53,615
所以他们总是能赢
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}That is why they will win.{\r}

160
00:14:53,824 --> 00:14:57,995
雷山德，我记得头儿说要你交出武器的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Lysander, I thought the Sun ordered to surrender your weapons.{\r}

161
00:14:58,161 --> 00:14:59,955
他是说过
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}He did.{\r}

162
00:15:37,838 --> 00:15:39,799
现身
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Reveal yourself.{\r}

163
00:15:53,062 --> 00:15:54,606
给我现身
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Reveal yourself.{\r}

164
00:15:59,819 --> 00:16:02,739
- 父亲？　- 雅典娜！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Father... - Athena...{\r}

165
00:16:11,707 --> 00:16:13,625
- 宙斯　- 免礼
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Zeus... - No need for formalities.{\r}

166
00:16:15,669 --> 00:16:17,630
没有其他神注意到咱们吧？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}None of the other gods are looking?{\r}

167
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:19,632
是吧？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Are they?{\r}

168
00:16:21,614 --> 00:16:22,495
怎么？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What?{\r}

169
00:16:23,302 --> 00:16:25,012
刚刚你的样子
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}When you walked through here just now, {\r}

170
00:16:25,012 --> 00:16:26,722
真像个慈祥的父亲
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}you actually looked like a father...{\r}

171
00:16:27,723 --> 00:16:29,809
或者说更像一个祖父
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}...or maybe a grandfather.{\r}

172
00:16:31,603 --> 00:16:33,813
我们在这里必须小心
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}We must tread carefully here{\r}

173
00:16:34,063 --> 00:16:35,565
已经触犯天条了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}heed the law{\r}

174
00:16:35,732 --> 00:16:38,276
不能让凡人看见我们的神化之身
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}None of the mortals on earth should witness us in our immortal form.{\r}

175
00:16:38,693 --> 00:16:40,820
但父亲，你已经身处险境了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}But father, you've come dangerously close.{\r}

176
00:16:41,196 --> 00:16:43,907
你在这教导忒修斯已经多年了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You have been influencing the boy Theseus for years.{\r}

177
00:16:44,157 --> 00:16:45,784
我是扮成普通人的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}It is one of them{\r}

178
00:16:46,034 --> 00:16:48,370
不是以神的身份，就像他的一个朋友
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}never as a god.Only as his friend.{\r}

179
00:16:50,998 --> 00:16:52,332
为什么选他？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Why him?{\r}

180
00:16:57,546 --> 00:16:59,840
他不畏艰险
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}He does not fear danger.{\r}

181
00:17:00,674 --> 00:17:03,469
无视伤痛，不惧失败
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}No pain, defeat{\r}

182
00:17:03,803 --> 00:17:05,471
一往无前
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}or ridicule.{\r}

183
00:17:06,013 --> 00:17:07,431
他唯一担心的是
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}He fears only the failure to{\r}

184
00:17:07,431 --> 00:17:09,877
不能保护他所爱的人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}defend that which he holds so dear.{\r}

185
00:17:12,854 --> 00:17:14,772
至亲之人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}His loved ones.{\r}

186
00:17:15,023 --> 00:17:18,103
如果说有谁能带领他们对抗亥伯龙
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}If there is one human  who can lead them against Hyperion{\r}

187
00:17:19,653 --> 00:17:22,030
只能是忒修斯
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}It would be Theseus.{\r}

188
00:17:22,906 --> 00:17:25,033
但得靠他自己来抉择
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}But it must be his choice.{\r}

189
00:17:35,127 --> 00:17:41,008
他是叛变的，他要见国王
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}He defected. He wants to meet the king{\r}

190
00:18:52,624 --> 00:18:54,877
快走
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Move!{\r}

191
00:19:18,693 --> 00:19:21,626
你是那边来的逃兵
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You are a defector from what I understand.{\r}

192
00:19:23,198 --> 00:19:26,244
- 陛下，是的　- 我不是你的国王
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Yes, my king. - I am not your king.{\r}

193
00:19:27,452 --> 00:19:30,664
我希望你是
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I wish you to be.{\r}

194
00:19:31,665 --> 00:19:34,722
但你其实是个叛徒，不是吗？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}But you are a traitor by definition,are you not?{\r}

195
00:19:35,669 --> 00:19:39,905
我的军团要叛徒来干嘛？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What would I want with a traitor? In my midst.{\r}

196
00:19:40,841 --> 00:19:45,211
我可以告诉你哪个村庄没有布防
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I can you tell of a village, that lies unprotected,{\r}

197
00:19:45,513 --> 00:19:47,098
哪里你能找到年轻的女子
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}where you can gather young women...{\r}

198
00:19:47,306 --> 00:19:49,100
我已经有很多了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I have plenty of women.{\r}

199
00:19:49,392 --> 00:19:52,604
- 找到奴隶和武器　- 我也有很多武器
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Slaves and weaponry... - I have plenty of weapons.{\r}

200
00:19:54,606 --> 00:19:57,233
我想要的伊庇鲁斯之弓
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What I want is the Epirus Bow.{\r}

201
00:19:58,318 --> 00:19:59,819
就像这个地方
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Like this monastery{\r}

202
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:02,072
你们崇拜的这个圣殿
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I have moved every precious stone{\r}

203
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:04,032
我翻遍了的每一个角落
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}you people have worshipped upon...{\r}

204
00:20:08,287 --> 00:20:09,997
但仍然无法找到它
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}and I have yet to find it.{\r}

205
00:20:26,222 --> 00:20:28,933
你有见过赛伯琳祭司么，叛徒？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Have you ever met a Sybelline monk, traitor?{\r}

206
00:20:29,517 --> 00:20:34,547
这些祭司们盲目效忠于圣女先知
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}The monks of his order are unwavering in their obedience to the virgin oracle.{\r}

207
00:20:35,064 --> 00:20:39,360
只要手法到位，先知就能告诉我们那个弓在哪里
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}With the right prodding, the Oracle can see where the bow rests.{\r}

208
00:20:41,488 --> 00:20:43,805
她能找到是吧，祭司？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Couldn't she, Monk?{\r}

209
00:20:46,076 --> 00:20:47,911
告诉她在那
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Tell me where she is.{\r}

210
00:20:58,631 --> 00:21:00,959
我知道你们的信条，祭司
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I know your faith, Monk.{\r}

211
00:21:01,801 --> 00:21:05,346
赛伯琳祭司任何情况下都是不能杀人的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Sybellines are forbidden to take a life under any circumstance.{\r}

212
00:21:06,472 --> 00:21:08,057
包括自杀
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Even their own.{\r}

