{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Why would you do such a thing?{\r}

323
00:35:02,520 --> 00:35:05,607
就为个无名小卒铤而走险
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You risked your life to save a complete stranger.{\r}

324
00:35:06,149 --> 00:35:08,902
我想你应该没有信仰吧
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Only faithless man would ask such a question.{\r}

325
00:35:09,152 --> 00:35:11,446
我的母亲是个非常虔诚的信徒
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}My mother was woman of faith.{\r}

326
00:35:11,821 --> 00:35:14,866
即使她信仰的神往往对她视而不见
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}And her Gods were absent when she needed them the most.{\r}

327
00:35:21,748 --> 00:35:24,752
所以，我不信这些
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}As was I...{\r}

328
00:35:26,606 --> 00:35:27,713
所以我们就只能悲哀？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}So we both mourn?{\r}

329
00:35:30,674 --> 00:35:35,012
你对过去耿耿于怀，而我对将来忧心忡忡
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You, for what has past,and I, what is to come.{\r}

330
00:36:01,415 --> 00:36:03,625
这是怎么回事？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What happened to them?{\r}

331
00:36:06,691 --> 00:36:09,319
我下令谁都不许动她们
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I gave an order for them not to be touched.{\r}

332
00:36:09,527 --> 00:36:11,530
她们试图逃跑,我的国王
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}They tried to flee, my king.{\r}

333
00:36:12,155 --> 00:36:15,117
我们有七个好手都被他们杀了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Seven of our best men were killed in the struggle.{\r}

334
00:36:17,286 --> 00:36:20,956
七个好手被几个女人杀了？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Seven of your best men,killed by women?{\r}

335
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:25,753
我只想知道伊庇鲁斯之弓在哪
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I wish to know where the Epirus Bow rest.{\r}

336
00:36:30,257 --> 00:36:32,134
你们谁能告诉我吗？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Which of you can tell me this?{\r}

337
00:36:35,304 --> 00:36:38,516
谁是真的先知？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Which of you is the true Oracle?{\r}

338
00:36:44,564 --> 00:36:47,025
别逼我动用非常手段
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}If I am forced to search you out by other means,{\r}

339
00:36:47,275 --> 00:36:49,569
你们会感觉生不如死
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}you will experience disomfort.{\r}

340
00:36:50,612 --> 00:36:54,616
作为女性所不能忍受的侮辱
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Discomfort unique to your gender.{\r}

341
00:36:55,283 --> 00:36:56,827
所以，告诉我…
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}So you tell me{\r}

342
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:58,870
谁是真的？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}which one of you is her.{\r}

343
00:37:01,331 --> 00:37:03,417
我就是你要找的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I am the one you seek.{\r}

344
00:37:04,585 --> 00:37:06,587
不，是我
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}No, it is I.{\r}

345
00:37:07,213 --> 00:37:08,964
我才是你要找的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I am the one you seek.{\r}

346
00:37:10,925 --> 00:37:12,301
另外那个也这么说
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}The other one said the same thing{\r}

347
00:37:12,677 --> 00:37:14,679
都说自己是先知
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}They all claim to be the Oracle.{\r}

348
00:37:14,971 --> 00:37:16,389
另外的那个？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}-The other one?{\r}

349
00:37:16,681 --> 00:37:18,808
是的，我的国王
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Yes, my king.{\r}

350
00:37:19,434 --> 00:37:21,269
其他那个？哪一个？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}The other one? What other one?{\r}

351
00:37:21,519 --> 00:37:23,521
她们有四个人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}There were four of them.{\r}

352
00:37:24,063 --> 00:37:26,316
有一个跑掉了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}One of them escaped...{\r}

353
00:37:27,650 --> 00:37:30,820
和一帮水井边的奴隶一起
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}..With a group of slaves from the watering hole.{\r}

354
00:37:44,001 --> 00:37:46,337
- 蒙特刚　- 在
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Mantragkona! - Sire.{\r}

355
00:37:46,587 --> 00:37:48,255
把跑掉的那个找回来
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Find the one that escaped.{\r}

356
00:37:48,589 --> 00:37:50,091
我要活的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Bring her to me alive!{\r}

357
00:38:04,189 --> 00:38:05,732
黑海
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}The Dark seas..{\r}

358
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:10,612
这些水里尽是石油
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}These waters are thick with oil.{\r}

359
00:38:11,196 --> 00:38:12,614
那条什么船
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}and the boat?{\r}

360
00:38:12,823 --> 00:38:15,117
赫拉克里恩的普通商船
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}It's a Heraklian merchant ship.{\r}

361
00:38:15,409 --> 00:38:18,036
我们最好能把那船抢了，然后去南面
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Our best bet is to ambush it and head south.{\r}

362
00:38:18,328 --> 00:38:20,956
- 南面不是我们的目的地　- 对我来说是
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- South is not our journey. - Well it is for me.{\r}

363
00:38:25,336 --> 00:38:27,129
据我所知
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}From what I hear ...{\r}

364
00:38:27,338 --> 00:38:29,965
那边的妇女很容易丰衣足食
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}the women down there can get to the meat of a Malakian chestnut{\r}

365
00:38:30,174 --> 00:38:32,551
只要会点口活
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}... Only with their tongues.{\r}

366
00:38:35,096 --> 00:38:38,474
要不咱们试试你行不行，亲爱的？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Shall you and I test the limits of that desire, my dear?{\r}

367
00:38:40,727 --> 00:38:43,396
神给了我预知的能力
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}The gods have given me vision.{\r}

368
00:38:43,605 --> 00:38:45,982
而你只顾一己私欲
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Yet all you do is dream of your appetites{\r}

369
00:38:46,191 --> 00:38:47,901
我只管我是否满足
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I would rather follow my appetites,{\r}

370
00:38:47,901 --> 00:38:49,611
懒得理会你们是否欲求不满
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}than to follow hallucinations of a harlot.{\r}

371
00:38:49,778 --> 00:38:51,947
- 她可是高级祭司　- 关我什么事
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- She's a high priestess - It doesn't matter to me{\r}

372
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:54,533
高阶祭司或妓女，我反正要去南面
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}A priestess or whore, I'm heading south.{\r}

373
00:39:01,748 --> 00:39:03,625
我说什么招惹你了？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Was it something I said?{\r}

374
00:39:04,960 --> 00:39:07,838
那么，我的朋友，你想怎样？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Well friend? What will it be?{\r}

375
00:39:08,130 --> 00:39:10,091
跟我去南边
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}South with me,{\r}

376
00:39:10,382 --> 00:39:12,218
或者你跟着…
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Or will you follow...{\r}

377
00:39:13,135 --> 00:39:15,179
这位女士吗？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}the lady?{\r}

378
00:39:15,638 --> 00:39:17,306
都不是
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Neither.{\r}

379
00:39:19,851 --> 00:39:21,561
我会乘船向北
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I'm taking that ship north{\r}

380
00:39:21,811 --> 00:39:23,855
去被亥伯龙军团占领的圣殿
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}to Hyperion's camp at the monastery.{\r}

381
00:39:26,483 --> 00:39:29,027
你的想法让我觉得你已经疯了，“殿下”
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Your saviour sounds a lot like a mad man to me, Your highness.{\r}

382
00:39:32,239 --> 00:39:33,824
不过呢
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Personally{\r}

383
00:39:34,116 --> 00:39:37,077
我宁愿和疯子一边，而不是和他对着干
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I would rather fight with a madman, than against him.{\r}

384
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:10,362
你看到了吗？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Are you minding this?{\r}

385
00:40:13,615 --> 00:40:16,660
这个就是宙斯常说的有为青年，是不是？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}That is the mortal your father so extolls,is it not?{\r}

386
00:40:23,167 --> 00:40:25,002
现在和先知在一起了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}And he is with the Oracle.{\r}

387
00:40:25,210 --> 00:40:28,964
波塞冬，如果宙斯起疑心，我们会帮你圆场的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Poseidon, if Zeus were to suspect you, we will come to your defense.{\r}

388
00:40:46,816 --> 00:40:48,777
掌舵！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}At the helm!{\r}

389
00:40:50,987 --> 00:40:53,031
你不是说这就是艘商船！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I thought you said this was a merchant ship!{\r}

390
00:40:54,282 --> 00:40:55,867
我想我说错了！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I guess I was wrong!{\r}

391
00:40:56,535 --> 00:40:59,329
海面似乎也太平静了点…
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}The sea has forever been an unpredictable domain...{\r}

392
00:41:19,434 --> 00:41:21,144
晴天霹雳的时候
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}When the cloudless skies thunders, stand fast!{\r}

393
00:41:21,978 --> 00:41:23,771
最好是躲起来
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}... Better to leave.{\r}

394
00:41:25,398 --> 00:41:27,359
- 现在就跳船！　- 稳住！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- We have to jump now! - Stand fast!{\r}

395
00:42:52,030 --> 00:42:54,408
你知道那浪不是冲我们来的
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You knew that wave would save us.{\r}

396
00:42:57,661 --> 00:43:00,122
我只看到在滔天巨浪
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What I see is only a glimmer{\r}

397
00:43:00,933 --> 00:43:02,635
冲着我们扑面而来
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}of what may come to pass.{\r}

398
00:43:04,205 --> 00:43:07,400
是你的行动拯救了大家
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Your actions & desires shape what lies ahead.{\r}

399
00:43:10,633 --> 00:43:12,551
你还看到什么了？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}What else have you seen?{\r}

400
00:43:17,473 --> 00:43:20,309
一个身体裹着床单，躺在石头上
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}A body wrapped in a shroud, on a rock.{\r}

401
00:43:21,436 --> 00:43:24,272
你拿着伊庇鲁斯之弓
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You holding the Epirus Bow and...{\r}

402
00:43:30,362 --> 00:43:32,489
而且，你归顺了亥伯龙
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}embracing Hyperion.{\r}

403
00:43:32,697 --> 00:43:33,824
不可能！
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Impossible!{\r}

404
00:43:34,032 --> 00:43:35,867
我永远不会归顺于他
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I would not embrace Hyperion!{\r}

405
00:43:37,160 --> 00:43:38,829
他杀害了我的母亲
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}He killed my mother.{\r}

406
00:43:39,913 --> 00:43:41,582
你母亲？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Your mother?{\r}

407
00:43:42,666 --> 00:43:46,003
你看见她被埋葬了吗？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Was she given a proper burial?{\r}

408
00:43:47,630 --> 00:43:49,215
没有
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}No.{\r}

409
00:43:49,882 --> 00:43:51,926
她仍然在她被杀害的地方
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}No. She still lies where Hyperion cut her down.{\r}

410
00:43:52,468 --> 00:43:57,306
那你必须亲手埋葬她，这是她的信仰
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Then you must bury your mother.Her faith demands it{\r}

411
00:43:58,182 --> 00:44:00,018
我才不信仰那些神
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I do not believe in the gods.{\r}

412
00:44:00,309 --> 00:44:02,228
但她信仰
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}But she believed.{\r}

413
00:44:03,438 --> 00:44:06,524
她虔诚的信仰，忒修斯
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}She believed, Theseus.{\r}

414
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:09,945
你必须回到你们村
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You must return to your village.{\r}

415
00:44:31,801 --> 00:44:33,719
找到先知没有？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Have you found the Oracle?{\r}

416
00:44:34,011 --> 00:44:37,306
找到了，但是守卫在我们赶到之前被杀光了
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}We did my lord, But our men were lost before we could recover her.{\r}

417
00:44:37,682 --> 00:44:40,226
一场风暴要了他们的命
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}A storm swept them to sea.{\r}

418
00:44:41,102 --> 00:44:43,104
先知呢？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}And the Oracle?{\r}

419
00:44:44,189 --> 00:44:45,982
她活下来没有？
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Did she survive?{\r}

420
00:44:46,232 --> 00:44:49,069
她正前往科珀斯海湾，和几个奴隶一起
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}She travels towards Kolpos with the slaves.{\r}

421
00:44:49,319 --> 00:44:51,446
她可能是带他们去找神弓
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}She could be leading them to the Bow.{\r}

422
00:44:59,288 --> 00:45:01,874
让牛头怪到科珀斯海湾那边去
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Send the beast to Kolpos.{\r}

423
00:45:02,291 --> 00:45:05,085
我们现在出发去地狱山
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}We will go to Tartarus.{\r}

424
00:45:05,377 --> 00:45:07,338
- 蒙特刚？　- 主人
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}- Montragkonie? - sire{\r}

425
00:45:07,546 --> 00:45:09,340
你留守圣殿
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}You stay here.{\r}

426
00:45:10,174 --> 00:45:12,593
在矿坑里设好埋伏
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}Set an ambush in the pit{\r}

427
00:46:42,478 --> 00:46:45,148
对不起，我没有保护好你，妈妈
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}I'm sorry I couldn't protect you mother.{\r}

428
00:46:49,945 --> 00:46:53,364
但我向你保证我会好好活下去
{\bord0\shad0\fscx75\fscy75\1c&HFF8000&\b0}But I promise you our family name will not die with me.{\r}

429
00:51:48,964 --> 00:51:52,072
亥伯龙的军团正在地狱山集结
